Griffin====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"Center\" |'''Week No.'''\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"Center\" |'''Dance/Song'''\n! colspan=\"4\" align=\"Center\" |'''Judges' score'''\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"Center\" |'''Total'''\n! rowspan=\"2\" align=\"Center\" |'''Result'''\n|-\n|-\n! style= width=\"10%\" align=\"center\" |Revel Horwood\n! style= width=\"10%\" align=\"center\" |Mabuse \n! style= width=\"10%\" align=\"center\" |Ballas\n! style= width=\"10%\" align=\"center\" |Tonioli\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |1\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |[[Foxtrot]] / \"[[Build Me Up Buttercup]]\u201d\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 8\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 8\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 30\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | No Elimination\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |2\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |[[Jive (dance)|Jive]] / \"[[Dance with Me Tonight]]\u201d\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 6\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 27\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | Safe\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |3\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |[[Street dance|Street]] / \"[[Friend Like Me]]\" (2019)\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 9\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 36\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | Safe\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 4\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" |[[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]] / \"[[Dancing with a Stranger]]\"\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 6\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 7\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | 27\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\" | Eliminated\n|}\n\n;Notes\n:{{note|a|a}} [[Alfonso Ribeiro]] filled in for Tonioli\n\n====Christmas Specials====\nIn 2017, Buswell appeared on the Christmas Special and danced with footballer [[Robbie Savage]].<ref>\n{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/strictlycomedancing/entries/0faa2806-08fe-4c83-bb5e-91327a86f55c|title=Strictly Christmas line-up announced|website=BBC Blogs|language=en-US}}</ref> In November 2019, it was announced that Joe Sugg would be taking part in the 2019 special partnered with Buswell.<ref>\n{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/strictlycomedancing/entries/de5329a6-1c90-4698-ad82-3f58a731acb1|title=Meet the Strictly Celebrities for Christmas 2019!|website=BBC Blogs|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/strictlycomedancing/entries/3f55b623-ff2e-4ba0-b6b9-c83e3a032c5f|title=Meet the professional dancers for our Christmas Special 2019!|website=BBC Blogs|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn late 2018, Buswell began dating [[Joe Sugg]], her celebrity partner from [[Strictly Come Dancing (series 16)|''Strictly Come Dancing'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/12/31/joe-sugg-dianne-buswell-reunite-cute-couples-karaoke-session-just-time-new-years-8297960/|title=Joe Sugg and Dianne Buswell are reunited just before New Year's Day strikes|last=Pearce|first=Tilly|date=31 December 2018|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Twitter|id=dbuzz6589|name=Dianne Buswell}}\n* [https://www.instagram.com/diannebuswell/?hl=en Dianne Buswell] on [[Instagram]]\n{{Strictly Come Dancing}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buswell, Dianne}}\n[[Category:Australian ballroom dancers]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian dancers]]\n[[Category:People from Bunbury, Western Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Australian ballroom dancer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox dancer\n| name          = Dianne Buswell\n| image         = Dianne Buswell 2020.jpg\n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = Buswell in 2020\n| birth_name    = Dianne Claire Buswell<ref name=\"Vlog4Jan19\">{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jBSkBlsPYfA |title=What's in the box prank! |last=Sugg |first=Joe |date=4 January 2019 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Google]] |access-date=4 January 2019 |quote=}}</ref>\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1989|05|06|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Bunbury, Western Australia]]\n| partner       = [[Joe Sugg]] (2018\u2013)\n| nationality   = \n| citizenship   = \n| education     = \n| occupation    = Professional Dancer\n| years_active  = 2011\u2013present\n| home_town     = Bunbury, Western Australia\n| height        = <!--{{cvt|5|ft|5|in|cm|abbr=on}} Hidden until a reliable source is provided-->\n| current_group = \n| former_groups = \n| dances        = \n| website       = \n| module        =\n\n}}\n\n'''Dianne Claire Buswell''' (born 6 May 1989) is an Australian ballroom dancer. She was a professional dancer on the Australian version of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (Australian TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' in 2015. Buswell became a professional dancer on the British series ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' in 2017, being partnered with Reverend [[Richard Coles]]. In the 2018 series, she reached the final with her celebrity partner [[Joe Sugg]]. In 2019, she was partnered with [[Dev Griffin]].\n\n== Early life ==\nDianne Buswell was born in [[Bunbury, Western Australia]], [[Australia]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bunburymail.com.au/story/4746380/bunbury-dancer-to-compete-on-british-tv-show/|title=Bunbury dancer to compete on British TV show|last=Elstermann|first=Andrew|date=22 June 2017|work=Bunbury Mail|access-date=9 September 2017}}</ref> She started ballroom dancing at age 4.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burnthefloor.com:80/dianne-buswell/|title=Dianne Buswell {{!}} Burn The Floor|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606234055/http://www.burnthefloor.com/dianne-buswell/|archive-date=6 June 2014|url-status=dead|access-date=9 September 2017}}\n</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nDianne and her brother Andrew Buswell<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dancescenewa.org.au/index.php/2015-10-05-13-13-56/dancer-profile-listings/13-andrew-buswell-profile |title=Dancer Profile Listings: Andrew Buswell |access-date=1 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001215801/http://www.dancescenewa.org.au/index.php/2015-10-05-13-13-56/dancer-profile-listings/13-andrew-buswell-profile |archive-date=1 October 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> were Adult New Vogue WA Champions for 2008 and 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dancesport.org.au/index.php/123-western-australia-information/champions-of-the-past|title=DanceSport Australia|website=dancesport.org.au|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403181514/http://www.dancesport.org.au/index.php/123-western-australia-information/champions-of-the-past|archive-date=2015-04-03|url-status=dead|access-date=1 July 2017}}</ref> She also appeared on ''[[So You Think You Can Dance Australia]]''.<ref name=\":1\" /> Buswell joined the live dance show ''[[Burn the Floor]]'' in January 2011.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/strictlycomedancing/entries/a8f6012a-b783-4fdb-ac7b-a995ef2cb4b7|title=Three new sensational dancers join our professional dancer line up for 2017|date=21 June 2017|website=Strictly Come Dancing|access-date=9 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> She joined Australia's ''[[Dancing with the Stars (Australian TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' in 2015, paired with Australian AFL star [[Jude Bolton]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mediaweek.com.au/dancing-with-the-stars-celebrities-revealed/|title=Dancing with the Stars celebrities revealed \u2013 Mediaweek|date=6 July 2015|website=mediaweek.com.au|access-date=1 July 2017}}</ref> they were the fifth couple eliminated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thewest.com.au/news/wa/dianne-judes-swan-song-ng-ya-393127|title=Dianne & Jude's swan song|last=South Western Times|date=22 August 2015|work=The West Australian|access-date=9 September 2017}}</ref> Following her elimination from ''Dancing with the Stars'', Buswell rejoined the ''Burn the Floor'' tour.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== ''Strictly Come Dancing'' ===\nBuswell joined the [[BBC]]'s ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' in 2017.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> Her celebrity partner for the [[Strictly Come Dancing (series 15)|2017 series]] was the Reverend [[Richard Coles]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/09/09/strictly-come-dancing-2017s-pairings-are-revealed-but-whos-dancing-with-who-6915098/|title=Strictly Come Dancing 2017's pairings are revealed \u2013 but who's dancing with who?|last=Westbrook|first=Caroline|date=9 September 2017|website=Metro|access-date=9 September 2017}}</ref> They were the second couple eliminated in the series, losing the dance-off to [[Simon Rimmer]] and [[Karen Clifton]] in a unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/10/08/reverend-richard-coles-makes-an-early-exit-from-strictly-after-becoming-the-second-celebrity-to-leave-6984965/|title=Strictly Come Dancing 2017's second celebrity has left the ballroom|last=Westbrook|first=Caroline|date=8 October 2017|work=Metro|access-date=8 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe was paired with television presenter [[Tim Vincent]] for ''Strictly Come Dancing''{{'s}} 2017 Children in Need special.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/strictly-come-dancing/336915-strictly-come-dancing-children-need-cast-2017.html|title=Strictly Come Dancing Children in Need line up 2017 REVEALED|date=24 October 2017|work=TellyMix|access-date=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nFor the [[Strictly Come Dancing (series 16)|sixteenth series]] of the show in 2018, she was paired with [[Joe Sugg]], in which they were runners-up alongside [[Faye Tozer]] and [[Giovanni Pernice]] and [[Ashley Roberts]] and [[Pasha Kovalev]], losing to [[Stacey Dooley]] and [[Kevin Clifton]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-09-09/strictly-come-dancing-2018-joe-sugg-party-birthday/ |title=Joe Sugg invited all the Strictly Come Dancing celebrities to his house to watch first show of the series |last=Gill |first=James |date=9 September 2018 |work=[[Radio Times]] |publisher= |access-date=10 September 2018 |quote=}}</ref> In December 2018, Buswell was announced to be joining the 'Strictly Come Dancing Live!' tour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://strictlycomedancinglive.com/2018/12/full-tour-line-up-announced-for-strictly-come-dancing-live/|title=Strictly Come Dancing Live! The Line Up|website=Strictly Come Dancing Live!|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref> Alongside her partner Joe Sugg, they won more shows on the tour than any other couple that year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Btt1fi0BRnt/|title=Strictly Come Dancing Live on Instagram: \u201cAnd the winners of the final 2019 @strictlycomedancinglive show were... @joe_sugg and @diannebuswell With a phenomenal 28/29 tour wins\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/joe-suggs-fans-accused-fixing-13960088|title=Strictly star Joe Sugg has won all 20 shows of the Strictly tour|last=Freedman|first=Joanna S.|date=2019-02-06|website=mirror|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/film/2019021067720/strictly-come-dancing-live-tour-winners-2019/|title=The overall winners of the Strictly Come Dancing tour have been announced \u2013 and it's not Stacey Dooley!|date=2019-02-10|website=HELLO!|language=en|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref>\n\nBuswell returned for her third series in 2019, paired with radio DJ [[Dev Griffin]]. They were the third couple to leave the show, after losing a dance-off to [[Emma Weymouth]] and [[Alja\u017e Skorjanec]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bbcstrictly/status/1183109439441854466|title=There's a high volume of calls tonight, so if you don't get though first time keep trying! And remember you can vote online.|last=Strictly \u00a0\u2728|first=B. B. C.|date=2019-10-12|website=@bbcstrictly|language=en|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/strictly-fix-claims-furious-fans-20572786|title=Strictly fix scandal as furious fans claim they couldn't vote for axed couple|last=Hill|first=Rose|date=2019-10-13|website=mirror|access-date=2019-10-18}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Series\n! Partner\n! Place\n! Average<br>Score\n|-\n|[[Strictly Come Dancing (series 15)|15]]\n|[[Richard Coles|Reverend Richard Coles]]\n|14th\n|16.0\n|-style=\"text-align:center; background:#ccc;\"\n|[[Strictly Come Dancing (series 16)|16]]\n|[[Joe Sugg]]\n|2nd\n|32.8\n|-\n|[[Strictly Come Dancing (series 17)|17]]\n|[[Dev Griffin]]\n|13th\n|30.0\n|}\n\nIn the following tables, ''{{Red|red text}}'' indicates the couple(s) with the lowest score for that week.\n\n====Series 15: with Reverend Richard Coles ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" alig