{"title_page": "Petr Tat\u00ed\u010dek", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| caption = \n| alt = \n| image = Petr_Taticek_ERC.jpg\n| image_size = 230px\n| team = [[ERC Ingolstadt]]\n| league = [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga|DEL]]\n| former_teams = [[HC Kladno]]<br>[[Florida Panthers]]<br>[[HC Davos]]<br>[[HC Lev Praha]]\n| position = [[Centre (ice hockey)|Centre]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 2\n| weight_lb = 190 \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|9|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Rakovn\u00edk]], [[Czechoslovakia]]\n| draft = 9th overall\n| draft_year = 2002\n| draft_team = [[Florida Panthers]]\n| career_start = 2000\n}}\n\n'''Petr Tat\u00ed\u010dek''' (born 22 September 1983) is a [[Czechs|Czech]] professional [[ice hockey]] [[Centre (ice hockey)|centre]] currently playing for [[ERC Ingolstadt]] of the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] (DEL). He previously played for the [[Florida Panthers]] of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL).\n\n==Playing career==\nTat\u00ed\u010dek was drafted ninth overall by the [[Florida Panthers]] in the [[2002 NHL Entry Draft]] from the [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] of the [[Ontario Hockey League]] (OHL) and played just three games for the Panthers during the [[2005\u201306 NHL season]], going pointless. On 9 March 2006, Tat\u00ed\u010dek was traded to the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] in exchange for [[Richard Jackman]], but never played for them, spending the remainder of the season with their [[American Hockey League]] (AHL) affiliate, the [[Wilkes-Barre/Scranton Penguins]].\n\nTat\u00ed\u010dek then signed with the [[Washington Capitals]] as a free agent, but only played one game for their AHL affiliate, the [[Hershey Bears]], before returning to the [[Czech Extraliga]] with [[HC Kladno]]. Later in the season, he moved to [[HC Davos]] of the Swiss [[National League A|Nationalliga A]].\n\nOn 22 July 2014, Tat\u00ed\u010dek signed as a one-year contract as a free agent with [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]] (DEL) club [[ERC Ingolstadt]]. On 23 November 2014, during the [[2014\u201315 DEL season|2014\u201315]] season, and having quickly adapted to the DEL and among the team's top scoring line, Tat\u00ed\u010dek was signed to a three-year contract extension to remain in Ingolstadt.<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.erc-ingolstadt.de/profis/newsdetail?id=3045 | title = ERC Ingolstadt extends Taticek to 2018 | publisher = [[ERC Ingolstadt]] | date = 2014-11-23 | accessdate = 2014-11-23  | language = German}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Regular season and playoffs===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Regular season]] \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Playoffs]] \n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! [[Season (sports)|Season]] \n! Team \n! League \n! GP \n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]] \n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]] \n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]] \n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]] \n! GP\n! G \n! A \n! Pts \n! PIM \n|-\n| 1999\u201300\n| [[HC Kladno]]\n| Czech.20\n| 44\n| 8\n| 16\n| 24\n| 22\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[1999\u20132000 Czech Extraliga season|1999\u201300]]\n| HC Kladno\n| [[Czech Extraliga|ELH]]\n| 4\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 4\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- \n| 2000\u201301\n| HC Kladno\n| Czech.20\n| 30\n| 7\n| 12\n| 19\n| 54\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[2000\u201301 Czech Extraliga season|2000\u201301]]\n| HC Kladno\n| ELH\n| 3\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n| [[2001\u201302 OHL season|2001\u201302]]\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]]\n| [[Ontario Hockey League|OHL]]\n| 60\n| 21\n| 42\n| 63\n| 32\n| 6\n| 3\n| 3\n| 6\n| 4\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[2002-03 OHL season|2002\u201303]]\n| Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds\n| OHL\n| 54\n| 12\n| 45\n| 57\n| 44\n| 4\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| [[2003\u201304 AHL season|2003\u201304]]\n| [[San Antonio Rampage]]\n| [[American Hockey League|AHL]]\n| 63\n| 4\n| 15\n| 19\n| 6\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| [[2004\u201305 AHL season|2004\u201305]]\n| San Antonio Rampage\n| AHL\n| 67\n| 7\n| 15\n| 22\n| 21\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n| [[2004\u201305 CHL season|2004\u201305]]\n| [[Laredo Bucks]]\n| [[Central Hockey League|CHL]]\n| 4\n| 2\n| 5\n| 7\n| 0\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| [[2005\u201306 AHL season|2005\u201306]]\n| [[Houston Aeros (1994\u20132013)|Houston Aeros]]\n| AHL\n| 44\n| 9\n| 21\n| 30\n| 10\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|-\n| [[2005\u201306 NHL season|2005\u201306]]\n| [[Florida Panthers]]\n| [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| 3\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| 2005\u201306\n| [[Wilkes-Barre/Scranton Penguins]]\n| AHL\n| 17\n| 4\n| 4\n| 8\n| 7\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 2\n|- \n| [[2006\u201307 AHL season|2006\u201307]]\n| [[Hershey Bears]]\n| AHL\n| 1\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 2\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| [[2006\u201307 Czech Extraliga season|2006\u201307]]\n| HC Kladno\n| ELH\n| 10\n| 0\n| 2\n| 2\n| 6\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- \n| [[2006\u201307 NLA season|2006\u201307]]\n| [[HC Davos]]\n| [[National League A|NLA]]\n| 15\n| 4\n| 1\n| 5\n| 8\n| 17\n| 3\n| 4\n| 7\n| 10\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| [[2007\u201308 NLA season|2007\u201308]]\n| HC Davos\n| NLA\n| 29\n| 6\n| 2\n| 8\n| 47\n| 12\n| 1\n| 6\n| 7\n| 2\n|- \n| [[2008\u201309 NLA season|2008\u201309]]\n| HC Davos\n| NLA\n| 50\n| 6\n| 15\n| 21\n| 20\n| 21\n| 4\n| 5\n| 9\n| 12\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" \n| [[2009\u201310 NLA season|2009\u201310]]\n| HC Davos\n| NLA\n| 48\n| 